  <h2>Who is {{name}}?</h2>
  <p class="section__description">Rob Bilotta is a disability rights and housing advocate who has been active in petitioning city for affordable housing and traffic calming measures. Bilotta ran for city council in 2023 after being heavily involved in the city's <a href="https://patch.com/massachusetts/worcester/rob-bilotta-runs-worcester-district-2-council-fresh-face" target="_blank">inclusionary zoning ordinance</a>. His top priorities, if elected, are creating more affordable housing, improving neighborhood infrastructure, and expanding STEM and special education programs.</p>

