  <section>
  <h2>What are {{name}}'s Political Positions?</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>Housing:</b> Bilotta supports several affordable housing policies, including rent stabilization, expanding first-time home buyer incentives, and legalizing accessory dwelling units (ADUs). He has petitioned city council to <a href="https://www.telegram.com/story/opinion/columns/guest/2025/03/16/opinionguest-column-worcesters-senior-housing-needs-new-leadership/81160150007/" target="_blank">expand Worcester's senior homeowner tax credit.</a> He supports real estate transfer fees on high-end real estate transactions to create dedicated funding for affordable housing. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Education:</b> Bilotta wants to work with Worcester's higher education institutions to increase PILOT contributions for STEM and special education programs. He opposes the expansion of charter schools. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup></b>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Police:</b> Bilotta supports the creation of an community-based emergency response program to respond to mental and behavioral health crises. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Immigration:</b> Bilotta wants to address ICE activity in Worcester by providing information to migrant communities to stay informed and know their rights. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Public Transportation:</b> Bilotta is in favor of making the <a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">fare-free WRTA program permanent</a>. A major pillar of Bilotta's campaign platform is improving neighborhood infrastructure, including sidewalks, crosswalks, lighting, signage, and other traffic calming measures. Rob has <a href="https://www.telegram.com/story/opinion/columns/guest/2024/08/18/robert-bilotta-on-clearing-obstacles-to-safer-streets-in-worcester/74780622007/" target="_blank">written about the importance of taffic safety</a>, and has submitted several petitions for traffic calming measures in his district. Bilotta supports the expansion of protected bike lanes across the city. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Sustainability:</b> Bilotta supports tax incentives for new construction using green technology, adopting building codes that would mandate new construction and renovations make use of modern, high-efficiency heating and cooling systems, as well as expanding the city's tree canopy. <sup><a href="{{surveyLink}}" target="_blank">source</a></sup>
    </li>

